summary: This is an FBI interview summary (FD-302) documenting an interview with Julio Cesar Suarez on November 2, 2009. Suarez was interviewed regarding his travel to a Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida, with his friend Alfredo Rodriguez, who was in possession of documents. The document records Suarez's statements and the release of Rodriguez's vehicle to Suarez.

persons.name: Julio Cesar Suarez
persons.context: Interviewed by FBI agents regarding his travel with Alfredo Rodriguez to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida. He is a U.S. Permanent Resident employed as a kitchen cabinet salesperson.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Friend of Suarez who drove him to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton. He was in possession of documents and requested his vehicle be released to Suarez after the interview. He rents the El Cristo restaurant in Miami.

connections.description: Friends who met through their wives. Rodriguez picked up Suarez to have lunch and drove him to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton.

events.title: FBI Interview of Julio Cesar Suarez
events.description: FBI agents interviewed Julio Cesar Suarez regarding his travel with Alfredo Rodriguez to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida. Suarez was advised of his rights and signed an FD-395 form.

events.title: Vehicle Release to Suarez
events.description: At the conclusion of the interview and at the request of Alfredo Rodriguez, Rodriguez's Chevrolet Trailblazer was released to Julio Cesar Suarez.

locations: El Cristo restaurant, 8th Street, Miami, Florida
keyFacts: Julio Cesar Suarez was interviewed by the FBI on November 2, 2009, in relation to his friend Alfredo Rodriguez.
Suarez traveled with Rodriguez to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida, where Rodriguez had documents, but Suarez denied knowledge of their contents.
Alfredo Rodriguez rents the El Cristo restaurant in Miami and had his vehicle released to Suarez after the interview.
The interview was part of FBI case number 72-MM-113327.
